Language: <F P=105> Serbo-Croatian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpts] Croatian President Franjo Tudjman has left for 
Washington. This afternoon, Central European time, he is to 
have talks with U.S. Secretary of State Warren Christopher. 
President Tudjman is also to open the Croatian Embassy in 
Washington today, about which THE WASHINGTON TIMES wrote 
yesterday. [passage omitted] 
  President Tudjman and Alija Izetbegovic are to sign bases 
for 
a confederal agreement between the Republic of Croatia and the 
federal Bosnia-Herzegovina tomorrow. He is also to attend a 
ceremony at which an agreement on the establishment of a 
federation between the Croats and the Bosniak Muslims in 
Bosnia-Herzegovina will be signed. 
  In Washington the Croatian president is also to meet 
President Clinton, representatives of the largest international 
financial organizations, journalists, and Croatian emigrants. 
In New York he is to meet United Nations Secretary General 
Butrus-Ghali. [passage omitted] 

